 ThreadPoolExecutor Life Cycle States
 ------------------------------------------------------
    RUNNING → SHUTDOWN → STOP → TIDYING → TERMINATED
    
 1. RUNNING
     - Initial state when the thread pool is created.	
     - Accepts new tasks
     - Processes queued tasks
         ThreadPoolExecutor executor = new ThreadPoolExecutor(...);
         
 2. SHUTDOWN
      - executor.shutdown();
      - Stops accepting new tasks
      - Continues processing tasks already in the queue
      
 3. STOP
      - executor.shutdownNow();
      - Stops accepting new tasks
      - Stops processing queued tasks
      - Interrupts running threads
      
 4. TIDYING
      - All tasks are completed
      - Worker threads are terminated
      - Pool is cleaning up resources
      - terminated() hook method is called
      
 5. TERMINATED
      - Thread pool is completely shut down
      - No threads
      - No tasks
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
